  {
    "type": "ListItem",
    "element_id": "b1fd852505a7254881e735b2714d3d5f",
    "text": "In this section, we show that state machines can be generalized to admit continuous inputs and outputs and to combine discrete and continuous dynamics.",
    "metadata": {
      "coordinates": {
        "points": [
          [
            46.38302830504534,
            149.28201751734377
          ],
          [
            46.38302830504534,
            268.34841919999997
          ],
          [
            625.0535663286719,
            268.34841919999997
          ],
          [
            625.0535663286719,
            149.28201751734377
          ]
        ],
        "system": "PixelSpace",
        "layout_width": 720.0,
        "layout_height": 540.0
      },
      "file_directory": "data\\raw\\Embedded",
      "filename": "Lec 4.pdf",
      "languages": [
        "eng"
      ],
      "last_modified": "2021-04-13T13:58:32",
      "page_number": 3,
      "parent_id": "2b7ce95f4d41b85458d2769aeb7eda96",
      "filetype": "application/pdf"
    }
  },
  {
    "type": "ListItem",
    "element_id": "489b5edc9af7a3eef5ccee7709b5b352",
    "text": "A hybrid system is sometimes called a modal model because it has a finite number of modes, one for each state of the FSM.",
    "metadata": {
      "coordinates": {
        "points": [
          [
            46.38302830504534,
            279.78202895734375
          ],
          [
            46.38302830504534,
            368.84844324
          ],
          [
            615.1070410232247,
            368.84844324
          ],
          [
            615.1070410232247,
            279.78202895734375
          ]
        ],
        "system": "PixelSpace",
        "layout_width": 720.0,
        "layout_height": 540.0
      },
      "file_directory": "data\\raw\\Embedded",
      "filename": "Lec 4.pdf",
      "languages": [
        "eng"
      ],
      "last_modified": "2021-04-13T13:58:32",
      "page_number": 3,
      "parent_id": "2b7ce95f4d41b85458d2769aeb7eda96",
      "filetype": "application/pdf"
    }
  },
