      "page_number": 4,
      "parent_id": "38d63a286f7da98b1d997916272a9257",
      "filetype": "application/pdf"
    }
  },
  {
    "type": "Title",
    "element_id": "5d3e3ffcc9141846a27142bbe2555dd8",
    "text": "What About Continuous Inputs?",
    "metadata": {
      "coordinates": {
        "points": [
          [
            56.698818,
            62.56259899999998
          ],
          [
            56.698818,
            106.56259899999998
          ],
          [
            642.46639554,
            106.56259899999998
          ],
          [
            642.46639554,
            62.56259899999998
          ]
        ],
        "system": "PixelSpace",
        "layout_width": 720.0,
        "layout_height": 540.0
      },
      "file_directory": "data\\raw\\Embedded",
      "filename": "Lec 4.pdf",
      "languages": [
        "eng"
      ],
      "last_modified": "2021-04-13T13:58:32",
      "page_number": 5,
      "filetype": "application/pdf"
    }
  },
  {
    "type": "ListItem",
    "element_id": "b9aab2072f87179677c6dc7442af0240",
    "text": "We have so far assumed that state machines operate in a sequence of discrete reactions. \u2022 We have assumed that inputs and outputs are absent between reactions.",
    "metadata": {
      "coordinates": {
        "points": [
          [
            46.38302830504534,
            149.28201751734377
          ],
          [
            46.38302830504534,
            278.84842484
          ],
          [
            597.0922237384941,
            278.84842484
          ],
          [
            597.0922237384941,
            149.28201751734377
          ]
        ],
        "system": "PixelSpace",
        "layout_width": 720.0,
        "layout_height": 540.0
      },
      "file_directory": "data\\raw\\Embedded",
      "filename": "Lec 4.pdf",
      "languages": [
        "eng"
      ],
      "last_modified": "2021-04-13T13:58:32",
      "page_number": 5,
      "parent_id": "5d3e3ffcc9141846a27142bbe2555dd8",
      "filetype": "application/pdf"
    }
  },
  {
    "type": "ListItem",
    "element_id": "ccf3d9cadf3209d3871ef123644d27b2",
    "text": "We will now generalize this to allow inputs and outputs to be continuous-time signals.",
    "metadata": {
      "coordinates": {
        "points": [
          [
            46.38302830504534,
            290.28202895734375
          ],
          [
            46.38302830504534,
            349.34843484
          ],
          [
            612.844581833416,
            349.34843484
          ],
          [
            612.844581833416,
            290.28202895734375
          ]
        ],
        "system": "PixelSpace",
        "layout_width": 720.0,
        "layout_height": 540.0
      },
      "file_directory": "data\\raw\\Embedded",
      "filename": "Lec 4.pdf",
      "languages": [
        "eng"
      ],
      "last_modified": "2021-04-13T13:58:32",
      "page_number": 5,
      "parent_id": "5d3e3ffcc9141846a27142bbe2555dd8",
      "filetype": "application/pdf"
    }
  },
  {
    "type": "ListItem",
    "element_id": "501173424001e6c1a02d8a9312377d2c",
    "text": "In order to get state machine models to coexist with time-based models, we need to interpret state transitions to occur on the same timeline used for the time-based portion of the system.",
    "metadata": {
      "coordinates": {
        "points": [
          [
            46.38302830504534,
            360.78202895734375
          ],
          [
            46.38302830504534,
            479.84844164000003
          ],
          [
            607.9123347988848,
            479.84844164000003
          ],
          [
            607.9123347988848,
            360.78202895734375
          ]
        ],
        "system": "PixelSpace",
        "layout_width": 720.0,
        "layout_height": 540.0
      },
      "file_directory": "data\\raw\\Embedded",
      "filename": "Lec 4.pdf",
      "languages": [
        "eng"
      ],
      "last_modified": "2021-04-13T13:58:32",
      "page_number": 5,
      "parent_id": "5d3e3ffcc9141846a27142bbe2555dd8",
      "filetype": "application/pdf"
    }
  },
  {
    "type": "Title",
    "element_id": "606f5fde43fd0576f62740645b3b9b73",
    "text": "Example 1",
